Reasoning: The paper deals with constructions of randomness extractors and tamper-resilient cryptography, which are topics in the subfield of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the analysis of the error and seed length of the extractors. The constructions involve combinatorial objects such as Ramsey graphs, which fall under the subfield of discrete mathematics (cs.DS). The paper also involves coding theory (cs.CC) in the construction of non-malleable codes. Finally, the paper involves complexity theory (cs.CY) in the analysis of the computational complexity of the constructions.
